# ND-120 Simulation Devices

This directory contains C++ implementations of peripheral devices that interface with the ND-120 CPU simulation through the Norsk Data Bus (ND BUS). These devices are integrated into the Verilator simulation and provide essential I/O capabilities for running the CPU self-test programs and bootstrapping the system.

## Overview

The simulation device framework allows the Verilog CPU to interact with I/O devices through memory-mapped registers, just as the real ND-120 hardware did. The devices respond to bus signals, handle interrupts, and provide timing-accurate behavior using delayed I/O callbacks.

